

                       AASSIGN FORMAT TO DRIVEN

               If  the "A" command is entered in answer to  the 
          system prompt "*", the computer will ask the operator 
          to select which DRIVE number is to be assigned. After 
          the  operator has selected the required DRIVE  number 
          the  computer  will  display the  list  of  available 
          FLOPPY numbers. The computer will ask the operator to 
          select  which FLOPPY number is to be assigned.  After 
          the operator has selected the required FLOPPY  number 
          the  computer  will  display the  list  of  available 
          FORMATS.  He  simply types the required FORMAT number 
          and presses RETURN. 

                              SYNTAX :-

                              A{d:fl,fm}

                 APRESS RETURN OR ENTER KEY FOR MAIN MENUN

